<document xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:z="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/z" source="Whatizit"><text><SENT sid="0" pm="."><plain>There are many <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0442893" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="">systemic diseases</z:e> in which eye signs detectable without an ophthalmoscope may be present </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="1" pm="."><plain>Examples are <z:hpo ids='HP_0001087'>congenital glaucoma</z:hpo> in <z:hpo ids='HP_0001067'>neurofibromatosis</z:hpo>, corneal involvement in <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0026948" disease_type="Neoplastic Process" abbrv="">mycosis fungoides</z:e>, <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0152276" disease_type="Neoplastic Process" abbrv="">chloroma</z:e> in <z:hpo ids='HP_0001909'>leukemia</z:hpo>, and <z:hpo ids='HP_0000554'>uveitis</z:hpo> and <z:hpo ids='HP_0000501'>glaucoma</z:hpo> in <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0019360" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="ZONA">herpes zoster</z:e> </plain></SENT>
</text></document>